== History == * In {{ill|1589|ja|1589th year|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1589|qq=}} ({{ill|Tenshō 17|ja|天正17th year|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tenshō 17|qq=}}), {{ill|Date Masamune|ja|伊達政宗|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Date Masamune|qq=}} expanded his influence into the {{ill|Iwase District|ja|岩瀬郡|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Iwase District|qq=}} region and demanded the surrender of the {{ill|Nikaidō clan|ja|二階堂氏|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nikaidō clan|qq=}} at {{ill|Sukagawa Castle|ja|須賀川城|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sukagawa Castle|qq=}}. Enraged by this, the retainers and residents gathered on October 10th with torches in hand at {{ill|Tokayama|ja|十日山|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tokayama|qq=}}, east of the town, pledging to defend the castle at all costs. This event is considered the origin of the festival. * After the fall of Sukagawa Castle, the festival evolved into a ceremony to console the spirits of those who died in battle. Under new feudal rule, the festival was disguised as a "Mujina Hunt" to avoid interference from the rulers.<ref>[http://www.city.sukagawa.fukushima.jp/2727.htm Sukagawa Tourism Association - Origin of Taimatsu Akashi]</ref> * The festival was historically held on October 10th of the lunar calendar and later shifted to November 10th of the solar calendar. Since {{ill|1986|ja|1986年|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1986|qq=}}, it has been held on the second Saturday of November. * The sacred fire is taken from {{ill|Nikaido Shrine|ja|二階堂神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nikaido Shrine|qq=}} and carried through Sukagawa City to the event site at {{ill|Midori-gaoka Park|ja|翠ヶ丘公園|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Midori-gaoka Park|qq=}}. * In {{ill|1995|ja|1995th year|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1995|qq=}}, the festival was held a month earlier on October 14th to coincide with the "Fukushima Kokutai" event. * In {{ill|2011|ja|2011th year|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/2011|qq=}}, due to the effects of the {{ill|Fukushima nuclear accident|ja|福島第一原子力発電所事故|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Fukushima nuclear accident|qq=}}, local {{ill|Torreya nucifera|lt=kaya grass|ja|カヤ|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Torreya nucifera|qq=}} used for the torches was found to contain trace amounts of radioactive material. Materials were sourced from across Japan to continue the festival.<ref>[http://www.asahi.com/national/update/1112/TKY201111120409.html 'Fukushima's Sukagawa Hosts Taimatsu Akashi with Nationwide Material Support'] (Asahi.com, November 12, 2011)</ref><ref>[http://www.yomiuri.co.jp/national/news/20111113-OYT1T00264.htm 'Flames of Recovery Brighten Fukushima - Taimatsu Akashi Held'] (Yomiuri Online, November 13, 2011)</ref> * The {{ill|2020|ja|2020th year|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/2020|qq=}} and {{ill|2021|ja|2021st year|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/2021|qq=}} festivals were held without spectators to prevent the spread of COVID-19.
== Access == * Sukagawa City is about 1 hour from {{ill|Tokyo|ja|東京|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tokyo|qq=}} via the {{ill|Tōhoku Shinkansen|ja|東北新幹線|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tōhoku Shinkansen|qq=}} (transfer at {{ill|Koriyama Station (Fukushima)|ja|郡山駅|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Koriyama Station (Fukushima)|qq=}}), and approximately 1 hour 40 minutes from {{ill|Sendai|ja|仙台|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sendai|qq=}} or {{ill|Utsunomiya|ja|宇都宮市|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Utsunomiya|qq=}}. * 15-minute walk from {{ill|Sukagawa Station|ja|須賀川駅|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sukagawa Station|qq=}} (JR Line). * 5-minute drive from {{ill|Sukagawa Interchange|ja|須賀川インターチェンジ|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sukagawa Interchange|qq=}} on the {{ill|Tōhoku Expressway|ja|東北自動車道|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tōhoku Expressway|qq=}}. * Approximately 2,000 parking spaces are available near the venue.
== References ==
{{Reflist}} == See Also == * {{ill|Fire Festival|lt=Fire Festival|lt=Fire festival|ja|火祭り|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Fire festival|qq=}} * {{ill|Sukagawa, Fukushima|ja|福島県須賀川市|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sukagawa, Fukushima|qq=}} * {{ill|Japan's Three Great Fire Festivals|ja|日本三大火祭り|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Japan's Three Great Fire Festivals|qq=}}
== External Links == * [http://www.city.sukagawa.fukushima.jp/taimatsu/ Taimatsu Akashi (Sukagawa City)]
